aa(lp189
VIf you ever really want to get away from it all
p190
aVand see something that you have never seen,
p191
aVand have an excellent chance of seeing something
p192
aVno one has ever seen, get in a sub.
p193
aVYou climb in, seal the hatch, turn on a little oxygen,
p194
aVturn on the scrubber,
p195
aVwhich removes the CO2 in the air you breathe, and they chuck you overboard.
p196
aVDown you go. There's no connection to the surface
p197
aVapart from a pretty funky radio.
p198
aVAnd as you go down, the washing machine
p199
aVat the surface calms down.
p200
aVAnd it gets quiet.
p201
aVAnd it starts getting really nice.
p202
aVAnd as you go deeper, that lovely, blue water you were launched in
p203
aVgives way to darker and darker blue.
p204
aVAnd finally, it's a rich lavender,
p205
aVand after a couple of thousand feet, it's ink black.
