aa(lp220
VThe mid-ocean ridge is a huge mountain range,
p221
aV40,000 miles long, snaking around the entire globe.
p222
aVAnd they're big mountains, thousands of feet tall,
p223
aVsome of which are tens of thousands of feet
p224
aVand bust through the surface,
p225
aVcreating islands like Hawaii.
p226
aVAnd the top of this mountain range
p227
aVis splitting apart, creating a rift valley.
p228
aVAnd when you dive into that rift valley, that's where the action is
p229
aVbecause literally thousands of active volcanoes
p230
aVare going off at any point in time
p231
aVall along this 40,000 mile range.
p232
aVAnd as these tectonic plates are spreading apart,
p233
aVmagma, lava is coming up and filling those gaps,
p234
aVand you're looking land \u2014 new land \u2014
p235
aVbeing created right before your eyes.
p236
aVAnd over the tops of them is 3,000 to 4,000 meters of water
p237
aVcreating enormous pressure,
p238
aVforcing water down through the cracks toward the center of the earth,
p239
aVuntil it hits a magma chamber
p240
aVwhere it becomes superheated
p241
aVand supersaturated with minerals,
p242
aVreverses its flow and starts shooting back to the surface
p243
aVand is ejected out of the earth like a geyser at Yellowstone.
p244
aVIn fact, this whole area
p245
aVis like a Yellowstone National Park with all of the trimmings.
