aa(lp247
VAnd this vent fluid is about 600 or 700 degrees F.
p248
aVThe surrounding water is just a couple of degrees above freezing.
p249
aVSo it immediately cools,
p250
aVand it can no longer hold in suspension
p251
aVall of the material that it's dissolved,
p252
aVand it precipitates out, forming black smoke.
p253
aVAnd it forms these towers, these chimneys
p254
aVthat are 10, 20, 30 feet tall.
p255
aVAnd all along the sides of these chimneys
p256
aVis shimmering with heat and loaded with life.
p257
aVYou've got black smokers going all over the place
p258
aVand chimneys that have tube worms
p259
aVthat might be eight to 10 feet long.
p260
aVAnd out of the tops of these tube worms
p261
aVare these beautiful red plumes.
p262
aVAnd living amongst the tangle of tube worms
p263
aVis an entire community of animals:
p264
aVshrimp, fish, lobsters, crab,
p265
aVclams and swarms of arthropods
p266
aVthat are playing that dangerous game
p267
aVbetween over here is scalding hot and freezing cold.
